What is goTele?   goTele is an off-grid outdoor tracking device specifically for outdoor enthusiasts and their friends, families, and pets to experience safe and exciting adventures. Everyone can check all (at most 30) group members' real-time positions and trajectories in one map, communicate with each other by sending SMS texts, send SOS signals in an emergency, etc – all without using any smartphone service and data! goTele was developed and continuously optimized by our hard-working R&D team who has been spending countless days and nights working on its unique DS-SS technology since 2013.When to Use goTele？Besides common outdoor activities, goTele can also be widely used in the following scenarios:*Skiing and Snowboarding*Camping, Hiking and Hunting*Children and Pets Supervision*International Travels or Family Vacations*Team Activities, e.g. Road Trips*Outdoor Games, Cross Country Races, Cycling, Motorcycling*Festivals and Concerts*Emergency, Rescue and Disaster Relief*Boy/Girl Scouts Acitivies*Water Sports, e.g. Kayaking, RaftingHow Does goTele Work? Mesh and Our Core DS-SS TechnologyMesh requires fixed team formations to support its transmission network, therefore it is only suitable for military use. However, team formation is random in outdoor activities, making it difficult to form an effective Mesh transmission network; people always lose connection with each other even when they are apart in short distances. In addition, Mesh's high power consumption and short continuous working time proves that it is not the best choice for outdoor activities.In order to improve all these defects, goTele adopts revolutionary DS-SS technology because of its advantages in low power consumption, strong anti-interference ability, and high sensitivity of receiving signals. goTele's transmission distance is enhanced by 5 times, which is 3-5 times stronger than Mesh's. 1W of goTele's transmission distance is equivalent to 5W of a walkie-talkie. Furthermore, goTele has a unique communication protocol, which can easily support networking of up to 30 users.Independent Built-in GPS ModuleAfter a year of outdoor testing and intensive research, we decided to build a cutting-edge GPS module with the highest precision into goTele despite its high cost.goTele effectively tracks your position stably and continuously under any troublesome and emergent situation. It saves on smartphone power consumed by GPS positioning and greatly improves team safety in outdoor adventures, furthermore, the precision is higher than GPS inside the phone.Main FeaturesAll thoughtful functions of goTele are deliberately designed for the easiest and most convenient operation for your outdoor adventures, and we will introduce the main features for you as follows.Real-time TrackinggoTele app enables you to view and compare real-time locations and trajectories of all 30 teammates directly in the same map without sending requests to each other. Whether you’re watching the personalized avatar icon of your friends in the map during your trip or reviewing the saved trajectories record after trip, you’ll feel goTele rather interesting, and it can really bring more fun and happy memory for your trip.SOSOne SOS button is specifically designed on goTele device to enable its owner in trouble to send out SOS signals and real-time location to your teammates in case of emergencies (e.g. smartphone lost or with no power).Geo-FenceThe Geo-Fence function lets you monitor and protect your loved ones by simply setting a safety distance in the app (100, 200, 300, 500, 1000, 2000 and 3000 meters). When the goTele device is carried by your kids or pets, the app will alert you once they exceed the safety distance.Off-line MapgoTele provides the free using and downloading of the top 5 common high-definition off-line maps, which includes Google Satellite, Google Map, Google Relief, Open Cycle and Open Street.MessageYou can send messages, emojis, and real-time locations to your group members even when your smartphone is out of service. It makes sure that each group member gets connected at any time under any situation.Three ProofingsgoTele is a high-quality product that is designed with 3 types of protection. (IP67 waterproof, dustproof and shockproof). In addition, goTele can resist extreme weather conditions between -20℃ to 60℃.goTele on the MediaProduct SpecificationLatest ProgressWe have conducted field testing of goTele all over the world, including distributors and outdoor influencers from USA, Canada, Australia, Norway, Hungary, African countries, India, New Zealand and so on. We have achieved large-scale testing and mass production of goTele, which is already our second generation product, therefore goTele is undoubtedly a satisfactory product with thoughtful functions and high quality.Company IntroductionBeijing Tele Industry Information Technology Co., Ltd. was founded in December 2013. It is specialized in outdoor sports safety communication solutions.In virtue of our accumulated industry experience over years, we were awarded the following awards：
Beijing division champion of Chinese intelligent hardware competition in 2015;
The best business value award winner of China smart hardware competition;
China outdoor sports association designated supplier.
Our company is the standard setter of Chinese national digital walkie-talkie FDMA. Other core team members are experienced senior executives from well-known enterprises, including following companies and institutes:
Hytera, the Chinese leading private network company and global second private network company;
NOKIA Mobile Telecommunications;
Beijing Sougou Science and Technology Development Co., Ltd;
Synertone Communication Corporation, the private network leader for Chinese army;
Chinese famous research institutes.
Product IterationTime LineFAQ1.Where can I download the goTele app? You can download the app in goTele official website, App Store, and Google Play, by simply searching “goTele”. Or, you can scan the QR code behind the goTele devices.2.How to fix goTele GPS signal?The goTele device can be paired and searched by goTele app with smartphone inside the building, while the goTele GPS signal has to be fixed outside building in the open air. 3.How does goTele work? goTele network works well by its devices and powerful app.Each goTele device has GPS and transmitters and receivers inside itself, and needn’t relay stations to transmit. Each goTele can send and receive information within a direct point-to-point transmission range. As long as the devices are in the transmission range of each other, they can send locations to each other and communicate with each other, creating a safe private wireless network.The app is used for displaying and realizing all functions, such as connecting and searching devices, creating group, selecting maps, recording management, displaying all users’ locations, walking distance, recording time, sending text, SOS alerts, showing remaining power, setting geo-fence distance, saving trajectories and so on. 4.Shall I pay extra charges for goTele from service provider? No, apart from goTele device itself, you don’t need to pay any extra fees.5.How long is the warranty of goTele?All goTele devices provide 1 year limited warranty.6.How to charge the goTele and how long is its battery life?goTele can be charged with any standard micro USB cable through a USB port, standard USB charger or portable source. If goTele is charged for 3-4 hours, it will continuously work for 48+ hours. 7.How does goTele do real-time tracking?Each goTele device consistently send out its GPS location through radio signal, and all the other goTele devices will soon receive it and store the location, then the app display all the locations simultaneously and link them up to form a trajectory.8.Can goTele work at anywhere in the world?There is no geographical restraint on goTele’s operation area, but it is necessary to understand the radio laws and regulations of the area before using it. The GPS satellites are for global use, as long as this area covered by GPS signal, goTele will work normally.9.How to know if I need a goTele app or not?goTele can work independently without pairing to phone and use app, if one (children or pets) doesn’t have a smartphone and needn’t to view other team members’ locations, he/she/it just need to take goTele device and needn’t to download app, as other users in the team with app can check the location of that user.  However, you still need the app in the following situations:- When you pair your goTele with your own smart phone as a group leader;- When you want to view your team members’ locations and trajectories; - When you want to receive the SOS signals. 10.Can I save trajectory of each trip?Yes, you can save the record of your and all other members’ trajectories for your trip.11.What’s the difference between goTele app and Google Maps app?Except own location tracking, goTele can display all group users' locations, but Google Maps app cannot do this. goTele also has other functions such as SOS and geo-fence etc.12.How do goTele members share their locations?After your friends, family, or pets are added to your group, goTele app will automatically display all their locations on the same map.After joining the group, you can send your text and current location through team chat function to all team members manually.If someone presses the SOS button, the app will send a SOS signal to all members on the sender's location, even if the sender doesn't download the app.13.Has goTele been approved by the FCC?Yes, goTele has been FCC approved.14.Who can receive the SOS signal?Every member in your group who have paired goTele with smart phone and has goTele app can receive SOS signals.15.How far is the transmission range of goTele? It’s about 3-5 Km (1.8-3.1 miles) in the open wild, 1-3 Km (.6-1.8 miles) in the city, and it changes slightly and depends on different terrain and environment conditions as mountains, trees and buildings will block the signal.16.Can you explain the differences between goTele and other outdoor communication products?Their differences are displayed in the following pictures:
